            . I am the wife of John Heath. I live in <placeName id="t18310908-238-crimeloc1221">White Conduit-fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-238-crimeloc1221" type="placeName" value="White Conduit-fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-238-crimeloc1221" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-238-off1219 t18310908-238-crimeloc1221"></join>. On the 3rd of September I hung a rug and table-cover on the rails of my door while I was sweeping the passage; the prisoner had been standing about the street some time - I saw him stoop down at the door, as I thought, to catch the cat; in a minute my neighbour said, "That man has taken your things" - I pursued and saw him with them on his right arm - I said,"Put them down" - he threw out his left hand, and struck me across the throat, but I still pursued, calling Stop thief! and he was secured.</p>
               <p>
            
